name: Hannaford Supermarket
directions: There are 2 unisex bathrooms located to the right of the service desk along the side wall. Both have changing tables, but currently only the one closer to the Service Desk is equipped for feminine hygiene product disposal/dispensing. Walk through the main doors, take a left towards the registers and you will see them next to the Service desk. If you get to the bakery, you are a bit too far ! Full disclosure, they are a bit hidden at first, but shouldn't be terrible to find !
comment: Free to use to the General Public, no purchase is required !

name: Walmart Supercenter #1856
comment: I am a Transman and have only used the Men’s room here. I would imagine the Women’s room to be safe as well. I have used this restroom from the beginning of my transition( pre T wearing binder dressed male) until now (3 yrs on T full beard still dressed male wearing binder) and I have NEVER had any trouble, comments or even an odd look. Because of that it is one of my preferred restrooms in town!

One is gender neutral, and the other is labeled “male”.
comment: You can’t park by the building if you aren’t a student, so park in visitor parking and walk/roll from there. You need a student ID after 9 pm
